cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the problem of adversarial examples in machine learning models, which is a common topic in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper proposes a new characteristic for evaluating fault tolerance, which could also be relevant to the sub-field of neural networks (cs.NE).
